MAKKAH: The Muslim World League has offered its condolences to the leadership, government, and people of Jordan, and families of the victims of a blast at the Red Sea port of Aqaba that left at least 13 people dead. Hundreds more were injured or suffered from the effects of gas inhalation after a crane loading chlorine tanks onto a ship on Monday dropped one of them. On behalf of the MWL, its Secretary-General Sheikh Mohammed bin Abdulkarim Al-Issa also wished the ill and wounded a speedy recovery.